Although I have to say I also prefer Cave shmups gameplay-wise, not just in terms of style, visuals and music. Although their style has also taken a nosedive in the past few years with some exceptions.

@Smuggy Misato That's what you have to put in patterns (to a degree) if you want players to actually utilize their reflexes or improvise. Otherwise everything just becomes pure routing/memorization, which is really boring imo. 

A pattern that has a few random variables that forces you to watch carefully and react each time while still employing careful strategy >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> doing the same thing every time

Even the guys back at Konami and Taito knew this. Gradius, Contra, and some Darius games are chalk full of random enemy behavior.
